name: Note about the int range
info:
Integers can be either passed as Numbers or as Strings. 
Due to javascript's Number format, the range of integers passed as Numbers is limited to the range between Number.MIN_SAFE_INTEGER and Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER.
Solidity can handle much larger or smaller integer values. Such values must be passed as strings to the node in order to be internally converted correctly to big numbers.
This is also the reason why the node will output integers as strings and not as numbers.

Contract call with transaction. Wait for Tx to be mined
info:
These calls wait for the contract call transaction to me minded before passing the message with the tx hash on to the next node.

Turn off the option 'Automine' in Ganache to see the difference between this and not waiting for the tx to be mined.

name: Contract call with transaction. Don't wait for Tx to be mined
info:
These calls DO NOT wait for the contract call transaction to me minded before passing the message with the tx hash on to the next node.

Turn off the option 'Automine' in Ganache to see the difference between this and not waiting for the tx to be mined.

name: Testing the simple error cases in the nonce managment
info:
Because the account 11 is not controlled by Ganache the node-red account config node has to do the nonce management. The nonce managment queue should not get corrupted by a rejected transaction and use the correct nonce for the next submitted transaction.

Not all possible cases are possible to test with Ganache and these test flows. Only 2 simple error cases.
Turn off the option "Automine" in Ganache for these tests.

Test1: 
Submitt for the next block:
1) tx without error
2) tx that fails during submission
3) tx without error
-> Both tx without error shoudl should yield a tx receipt.
-> More tx should be possible to submit.

Test2: 
Submitt for the next block:
1) tx without error
2) tx that throw error during mining
3) tx without error
-> All three tx should yield a tx receipt.
-> More tx should be possible to submit.

name: Estimate Gas
info: These nodes only estimate the gas of calls. Notice how no transaction hash is put out of the first ouput port. Because no transaction is made of course.

name: Use account that is not managed by the ganache node
info:
These calls use an account that is not managed by the ganache node.

For the VISEO-Nodes it makes no difference if Ganache manges an account or not. VISEO-Nodes always sign the transaction themselfes and therefore need the private key.

Notice how you won't be able to submit multiple transactions for the next block when the option 'Automine' is turned off in Ganache. This means the VISEO-Node does not manage the account nonce properly when submitting transactions.

Important: Make sure account 11 has some Ether to pay for the transaction before trying this out. Use the ether transfer below.

name: Read Ether balance
info: Notice how you can either set the address statically in the node configuration or dynamically in the input message.

name: Send Ether
info: Notice how you can either set the receiver address and wei amount statically in the node configuration or dynamically in the input message.

name: Send (10 Ether from Account 2 to Account 3)
Send (1 ETH from Account 2 to Account 11)
Fund Account 11 with some Ether if needed
!!! Contract calls won't work with abi  for solidity >= v0.5.0
Error Handling
info:
Notice how the error is written to the debug console AND also is caught by the catch node.
This would make it possible to impelement an error flow from the catch node, for instance do a retry or write the error to a database.

name: Contract call with transaction
info:
The first output port will send the transaction hash as soon as the transaction has been submitted to the ethereum node.
The second output port will send the transaction receipt as soon as the transaction has been mined.

Turn off the option 'Automine' in Ganache to see a time delay between these two outputs.

name: Fund Account 11 with some Ether if needed
Send (1 ETH from Account 2 to Account 11)
Use account that is not managed by the ganache node
info:
These calls use an account that is not managed by the ganache node.

It is possible to submit multiple transactions for the next block in any case.
The difference is, who manages the account private key and the accout nonce.
If the account is configured to be managed by Ganache then Ganache will do it. Otherwise the Node-RED red node config nodes do it.

Notice: 

Important: Make sure account 11 has some Ether to pay for the transaction before trying this out. Use the ether transfer below.

Error Handling
info:
Notice how the error is written to the debug console AND also is caught by the catch node.
This would make it possible to impelement an error flow from the catch node, for instance do a retry or write the error to a database.
